      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          I write the extended matrix with the original matrix and the
          identity.
          <me>
            \left( \begin{array}{ccc|ccc}
              0 \amp -5 \amp 2 \amp 1 \amp 0 \amp 0 \\
              3 \amp 0 \amp 1 \amp 0 \amp 1 \amp 0 \\
              0 \amp -4 \amp 1 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 1 
            \end{array} \right)
          </me>
          I row reduce this extended matrix.
          <me>
            \left( \begin{array}{ccc|ccc}
              1 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp \frac{-4}{9} \amp \frac{3}{9} \amp
              \frac{5}{9} \\
              0 \amp 1 \amp 0 \amp \frac{3}{9} \amp 0 \amp
              \frac{-6}{9} \\
              0 \amp 0 \amp 1 \amp \frac{12}{9} \amp 0 \amp
              \frac{-15}{9}
            \end{array} \right)
          </me>
          The left side reduces to the identity matrix, so the right
          side is the inverse matrix.  Then I check the two products.
          <md>
            <mrow>
              \frac{1}{9} \left( \begin{matrix}
                -4 \amp 3 \amp 5 \\
                3 \amp 0 \amp -6 \\
                12 \amp 0 \amp -15 
              \end{matrix} \right)
              \left( \begin{matrix}
              0 \amp -5 \amp 2 \\
              3 \amp 0 \amp 1 \\
              0 \amp -4 \amp 1
              \end{matrix} \right) = 
              \left( \begin{matrix}
                1 \amp 0 \amp 0 \\
                0 \amp 1 \amp 0 \\
                0 \amp 0 \amp 1 \\
              \end{matrix} \right)
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              \left( \begin{matrix}
              0 \amp -5 \amp 2 \\
              3 \amp 0 \amp 1 \\
              0 \amp -4 \amp 1
              \end{matrix} \right)
              \frac{1}{9} \left( \begin{matrix}
                -4 \amp 3 \amp 5 \\
                3 \amp 0 \amp -6 \\
                12 \amp 0 \amp -15 
              \end{matrix} \right) = 
              \left( \begin{matrix}
                1 \amp 0 \amp 0 \\
                0 \amp 1 \amp 0 \\
                0 \amp 0 \amp 1 \\
              \end{matrix} \right)
            </mrow>
