  <subsection xml:id="subsection-activity-transformations-of-spans">
    <title>Transformations of Spans</title>
    <activity>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Calculate the image of the given span under the given
          matrix. 
          <md>
            <mrow>
              \amp \Span \left\{ \left( \begin{matrix} 
                3 \\ -1 
              \end{matrix} \right) \right\} \amp \amp 
              \left( \begin{matrix}
                1 \amp -4 \\
                -2 \amp 4
              \end{matrix} \right) 
            </mrow>
          </md>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          To calculate the image of a span, I apply the matrix to
          each of the individual vectors. 
          <md>
            <mrow>
              \left( \begin{matrix}
                1 \amp -4 \\
                -2 \amp 4
              \end{matrix} \right) 
              \left( \begin{matrix}
                3 \\ -1 
              \end{matrix} \right) =
              \left( \begin{matrix}
                7 \\ -10
              \end{matrix} \right) 
            </mrow>
          </md>
          Then the image of the span is the span of the new vectors. 
          <me>
            \left( \begin{matrix}
              1 \amp -4 \\
              -2 \amp 4
            \end{matrix} \right) 
            \left[ \Span \left\{ \left( \begin{matrix} 
              3 \\ -1 
            \end{matrix} \right) \right\} \right] = 
            \Span \left\{ \left( \begin{matrix} 
              7 \\ -10
            \end{matrix} \right) \right\} 
          </me>
        </p>
      </solution>
    </activity>
